'''noun'''<br>
Any of several [[fruit]]s in the family Rutaceae, generally [[spherical]], [[oblate]], or [[prolate]], consisting of an outer [[gland]]ular skin called [[zest]], an inner white skin, and generally between 8 and 16 [[sector]]s filled with [[pulp]] consisting of cells with one end attached to the inner skin. Citrus fruits include [[orange]], [[grapefruit]], [[lemon]], [[lime]], and [[citron]].

